pshire, England":"Shrewsbury, Shropshire, England"},"en":{"1332–1400":"1332–1400","1327–1377":"1327–1377","1364–1404":"1364–1404","1368–1421":"1368–1421","1306–Male":"1306–Deceased","1316–Female":"1316–Deceased","1316":"1316","1404":"1404","1327":"1327","1368":"1368","1400":"1400","1377":"1377","1421":"1421","1332":"1332","1364":"1364","Abt 1368":"about 1368","1306":"1306","Evesham, Gloucestershire, England":"Tresham, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","St Giles Fields, London, England":"St Giles, London, England, United Kingdom","Almeley, Herefordshire, England":"Almeley, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Woebley, Herefordshire, England":"Weobley, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","Shrewsbury, Shropshire, England":"Shrewsbury, Shropshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Pembridge","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Pembridge (Herefs), which is recorded as  <i>Penebrug(g)e</i> from the 11th to 14th centuries. The place-name derives from an Old English personal name * <i>Pena</i> + Old English  <i>brycg</i> ‘bridge’. In some cases the surname may be from Pen Bridge in Shipley (Sussex), which derives from an uncertain first element + Old English  <i>brycg</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Pember","meanings":["English: perhaps a variant of <b>Pamber</b>, a habitational name from a place in Hampshire named Pamber, from Old English <i>penn</i> ‘fold, enclosure’ + <i>beorg</i> ‘hill’."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Pembridge was born in 1332, in Tresham, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Henry Pembridge, was 26 and her mother, Margaret de Sarnesfield, was 16. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Richard Oldcastle. She died in 1400, in Weobley, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 68."},"et":{"1332–1400":"1332–1400","1327–1377":"1327–1377","1364–1404":"1364–1404","1368–1421":"1368–1421","1306–Male":"1306–Surnud","1316–Female":"1316–Surnud","1316":"1316","1404":"1404","1327":"1327","1368":"1368","1400":"1400","1377":"1377","1421":"1421","1332":"1332","1364":"1364","Abt 1368":"umbes 1368","1306":"1306","Evesham, Gloucestershire, England":"Tresham, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","St Giles Fields, London, England":"St Giles, London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Almeley, Herefordshire, England":"Almeley, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Woebley, Herefordshire, England":"Weobley, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shrewsbury, Shropshire, England":"Shrewsbury, Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"1332–1400":"1332–1400","1327–1377":"1327–1377","1364–1404":"1364–1404","1368–1421":"1368–1421","1306–Male":"1306–Kuollut","1316–Female":"1316–Kuollut","1316":"1316","1404":"1404","1327":"1327","1368":"1368","1400":"1400","1377":"1377","1421":"1421","1332":"1332","1364":"1364","Abt 1368":"noin 1368","1306":"1306","Evesham, Gloucestershire, England":"Tresham, Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","St Giles Fields, London, England":"St Giles, London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Almeley, H